# Next.js App Router

## Version Warning

Next.js 16 has breaking changes. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next.js code.

## Structure

- `app/` — routing, layouts, page-level CSS only
- `app/page.tsx` — composes sections from `@/app/_components/`
- `app/layout.tsx` — fonts (`next/font/google`), metadata, global CSS
- `app/_components/` — page-specific UI (private folder, not routed)
- Shared reusable UI → root `components/` (e.g. `chart/`)

## Server vs Client

Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` at the top of files that need client features.

Current client components: `app/_components/sections/section-three.tsx`, `section-four.tsx`, `components/chart/radar-chart.tsx`, `hooks/use-decode-text.ts`.

## Images

Prefer `next/image`:

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";
import SparkPng from "@/public/images/spark.png";

<Image src={SparkPng} alt="Spark" />
// or
<Image src="/images/dino-1.png" alt="Dino" width={100} height={100} />
```

## Build Output

`next.config.ts` uses `output: "standalone"` for Docker deployment. Do not remove this setting.

## Not Used

Do not add unless explicitly requested:
- API routes (`app/api/`)
- Server Actions
- Middleware
- Dynamic routes or `Link` navigation
